text: Jacqueline Yvonne Harry, also known as Jackée, (born August 14, 1956) is an American actress, singer, comedian, and director. She is best known for her role as Sandra Clark 227. She is the first African-American to win an Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Comedy Series. ==References== == Other websites == * * Category:1956 births Category:American television directors Category:Living people Category:Participants in American reality television series Category:Emmy Award winning actors Category:African-American television actors Category:African-American movie actors Category:African- American stage actors Category:Actors from North Carolina Category:People from Winston-Salem, North Carolina
